		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">I suck at ldon<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Oct 29th 6:00 PM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10674684495776&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10674684495776&num=2&post=1&replyto=10674684495776"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=10674684495776></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=249517"><span id=>grumpass</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>25 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=grumpass&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I seem to suck at ldon and I need a little advice on how to improve my royal suckiness, not death causing suckiness, just in general sucking.&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all I am a level 50 paladin and this is my first character ever and I have soloed almost completly to get to 50.  In the last group I pissed everyone off. Between the magic effects, and the dead man floating on me and bad settings on my comp. I couldn't see anything it isn't a matter of not knowing what to do but at that pace I need some advice on settings for ldon to improve vision.  I already turned spell effects off and got some setting advice from the one person in the group with any sympathy.  Not being able to see and not knowing my way was making pulling impossible I think they thought I was just stupid.  Yes soothe, stun pull thanks for the tip but its a little hard when you can't see anything.  Next I have a habit of right clicking to look around for the next mob after killing a mob and I was not main loot I ended up looting about 15 times, not the items but the money and my split was on, at which point the entire group thought I was just a moron.  About halfway through the dungeon I made a conscious effort not to do it and moved away from the mob before looking around and broke that bad habit.  I have no problems grouping anywhere else and have decent gear I think the pace of ldon is hard to duplicate.  When the bard took over pulling and I fixed my settings a little and was main assist I caught all the mobs before they got a hit on him and very seldom lost agro.  but my skills still feel like they are subpar.  Any advice on where to practice the breakneck pace and any settings advice would be greatly welcome.  (I guess giving my 5 month old son a bottle while I am tanking in ldon would be a first step lol).  And no people in the group I didn't buy this character on ebay I do know how to play and got to level 50 the hard way but yes I do suck at ldon.  Only my third mission also.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Oct 30th 1:42 PM2003 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10674684495776&num=2&post=1&replyto=106753932216762"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=106753932216762></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=133177"><span id=Scholar>Ralston</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>257 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Ralston&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>First of all, don't be so hard on yourself :)<br><br>I've heard a LOT of people complain about not being able to see mobs in LDON dungeons. One thing that MIGHT help you would be to have Infravision cast on you inside the dungeons.<br><br>EQtools has downloadable LDON maps that you can unzip and extract to your UI Files folder.<br><br>That leaves us with the mobs. LDON dungeons are bad about having mobs hidden behind corners and such.<br><br>First, pacify everything you can SEE. That way, if you get jumped from behind a corner, you're not inviting all the mobs in the room to your party.<br><br>LDON IS fast paced, but IMHO, patience and efficiency is far more important that how fast the group moves thru the dungeon.<br><br>Some types of adventures require more rapid movement than others. The other night, me and some guildies did a slaughter mission. I pacified, pulled and tanked. Took my time, and just moved at a steady pace. We beat the dungeon with 36 minutes to spare and then completely cleared the dungeon before we got kicked.<br><br>I've found that groups I've been got in trouble from &quot;watching the clock&quot;. People get hasty and start taking risks.<br><br>And face it. You've only done 3 LDON's. You're in the learning curve. I'm sure your overall skills are fine. Since LDON, I play my Pally VERY differently than I did my first 56 levels.<br><br>LDON is a place for Pallies to shine. Already awesome tanks, able to heal, and effective against undead. Getting the pacify/pull routine down is all ya need to do. I'm a little biased, but a Paladin the the PERFECT LDON puller.<br><br>SO hang in there. Try and get your guildies to do LDON stuff. Pickup groups are a great way to find other good players, but LDON groups require HEAVY teamwork and everybody knowing their job. The best parties are those who are either experienced in LDON or those who play together a lot.<br><br>Just relax, and enjoy the fact that you can go into the MM LDON and own the zone :)<br><br>Ralston Purina<br>58 Mith Marr Knight<br>Prexus server</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Ralston Purina<br>Mith Marr Lord Protector<br>Prexus Server<br><br>"So many Undead. So Little Time"</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
