		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=149713"><span id=Scholar>ctbrew</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br>38 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.45]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=ctbrew&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Great advice from Ralston (great name Ral!), and I have a couple other questions/suggestions.&nbsp;&nbsp;First of all, what race are you? If no night vision get a permanent infravision item, there are many in the bazaar.  Secondly what resolution do you have your screen set to?  If its at the 800x600 yet, changing it to smaller resolution, which you can do in-game easily, makes a HUGE difference in how much you can see on your screen.  It just takes some getting used to.  I assume you've already moved up your clip plane and gamma settings.  Lastly, maybe a bigger monitor?<br>I've found that a well-set up interface makes a huge difference in how much you can see, especially in LDON.  If you have all your info (group chat, melee hits, spells being cast) going to the same window, it is really tough to keep up.  You need to separate these into different windows, and the windows will also be smaller preferably, giving you more viewing area.  How I have mine set up is, I have a chat box on the lower right coner, about 1/4 of the screen, which is strictly group chat, guild, /ooc's (my guild is small and doesn't talk that much, if they talk a lot set up a different window solely for guild chat, it can be distracting).  Then I have another window for spells only, mine, others, and melee warnings such as enrage.  That really is my &quot;main&quot; window I look at, makes it ez to interrupt casters that way.  I also changed the color of other's castings in that window to bright pink, so it really stands out when you need to caster interrupt.  In the upper right corner is my &quot;spam&quot; window, melee hits, which is a very small window which I rarely look at just to see how much I'm hitting.  It's amazing how much better I play when I am focused on what is going on group and mob-wise and not how much I am hitting for.  I have my spell, group, target windows down at the bottom of my screen, and buff window running vertically down the right side.  The point being keep the windows small and separate=more viewing area.  <br>IMO the right click to look around thing is mostly just while swimming.  I never use it, it's tough to control. Ral had good advice about LDON: take your time, check the corners, pacify if in doubt.  A good group should be able to handle one or two adds.  To save mana, if there is a chanty make a hotkey &quot;please pacify a %T&quot; and he'll assist you and pacify for you, so you can save your mana for stuns to keep aggro.  If you don't feel comfortable being the puller, someone else can do the same and you can /assist and pacify, then grab aggro from them after they have pulled (which you did with the bard).  K good luck.<br>Hallvard Leonidas<br>56 Knight<br>Morell-Thule</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=6&mid=10674684495776&num=2&post=1&mid=10674684495776><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">2 Posts [ <a href="/